How did we come to the conclusion that this is the way we wanted it?

In my head I had thought I would start by doing <component_type>/<vendor>_device.json, that exists on target in the same format.   That's fine we didn't do that, but at least some amount of discussion around why/how we're doing this is probably warranted.



as an aside on pushing this, I'd much rather we just squash all the move commits in a single commit, so we know they're all done, and we can discuss what the folder structure afterward looks like in a single review, rather than having to check out the series, and leave N comments on each one.

We should also get documented concretely what vendor means:  Is the the name of the manufacturer ODM of the component?  The name of the company of the person that pushes the config?  The name that it's branded as?  The name of the manufacturer field in the FRU?  Any of the above depending on disposition?  Regardless of which we pick, we should have a pointer for folks that add new configs.

Additionally, things like OCP NICs, GPUs, NVMe, and other things that get reused between manufacturers;  Whatever policy we pick, we should avoid duplication in those cases.

> How did we come to the conclusion that this is the way we wanted it?

The aim was somewhat selfish.  I'd like to be able to set OWNERs for the sub-directory for our hardware.  That would imply doing it on a vendor basis (because I don't think we want to enumerate every file in OWNERs).

>  I'd much rather we just squash all the move commits in a single commit,

Sure.  I can squash.

> We should also get documented concretely what vendor means:

I can write some words of what I think is most helpful.
See https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/entity-manager/+/74362 for "VENDOR.md".

> I'd like to be able to set OWNERs for the sub-directory for our hardware.

Yep, this is exactly the kind of thing that would be good to get in the commit message.  I'm assuming that's in the aforementioned commit, so I'm calling this good.
Pending the prior discussion on vendors.md.  LGTM
So this keeps the subdir on the BMC right?  Can the loader even find the files?
Currently it does not put them in a subdirectory on the BMC.
ok, good.
